Let hu(i) denote the probability of handovers to a near edge node ENi for the u-th user. Indeed, for each user a mobility proÔ¨Åle could be deÔ¨Åned, to estimate its movements with good precision. Furthermore, let us deÔ¨Åne a matrix P(u, n), which maps the user to the ENs according to the deployment of the relevant service instances. In this phase, we could assume that primary service instance and relevant replicas are equivalent.
The problem of managing replication management, such that both (i) the QoE degradation, i.e., the probability of reactive migrations, and (ii) the cost of replicas deployment are minimized, can be formulated according to the following linear program model:

